d equations of motion, hence of\nthe invariant action and, ultimately, of the fracton covariant symmetry.\nFinally, we increase the known analogies between LG and fracton theory by\nnoting that both satisfy the generalized Gauss constraint which underlies the\nlimited mobility property, which one would not expect in LG.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 3 Sep 2022 19:19:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 4 Nov 2022 09:41:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 17 Dec 2022 08:42:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-20"}
